comments.body:
This is `cause.foldLeft(None) { case (_, cause) if f.isDefinedAt(cause) => Some(f(cause)) }`, so find could be written as
```scala
private def find[Z](f: PartialFunction[Cause[E], Z]): Option[Z] = {
  f.lift(self) orElse foldLeft(None){ case (_, cause) if f.isDefinedAt(cause) => Some(f(cause)) }
```

Ha yeah right, you would need lazyness to get around that. Shame, that is elegant:
```scala
private def find[Z](f: PartialFunction[Cause[E], Z]): Option[Z] = {
  f.lift(self) orElse foldLeft(None){ case (z, cause) if f.isDefinedAt(cause) => z orElse Some(f(cause)) }
```
Out of curiosity, why a `PartialFunction` in `foldLeft`?

